    crossorigin="anonymous" referrerpolicy="no-referrer") 
  link(rel="stylesheet", href="/css/landingPage.css")
  link(rel="stylesheet", href="/css/index.css")
div(class="page guide-page")
  header(class="header")
    h1 Acquire
    div(class="navigation") 
      p Hi, #{playerName}!
      a(class="fa-solid.fa-house-chimney" href="/")
  h1(class="instruction-heading") HOW TO PLAY
  main(class="instruction-holder")
    h2 COMPONENTS OF GAME
    ul
      each val in ['Land (board)', 'Corporations', 'Tiles', 'Stock market', 'Stocks', 'Money', 'Information card']
        li= val
    h2 RULES  
    ul
      li At the beginning of the game, each player receives $6,000.
      li To determine who plays first, each player draws one tile and places it in its matching square on the board.
      li The player who has drawn the lowest number-letter combination starts play and players will play in ascending order.
      li Each player draws six tiles.
      li Each playerâ€™s turn consists of:
        ul 
          li Play a tile onto the gameboard by putting it on its matching space.
            ul 
              li Depending upon where a tile is played, it may form a corporation or it may merge two or more corporations.
          li Buy stocks of any active corporations. There is a limit of three total per turn.
          li Draw a new tile from the facedown cluster.
      li Ending the game When all active corporations are safe or one corporation has 41 or more tiles on the board.